<subSubSection id="C36F65575B77EC4CFF7D1DAAFEB0F885" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BCA36DC5B77EC4CFF7D1DAAFEB0F885" blockId="1.[151,1437,1581,2038]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis id="B901EACE5B77EC4CFF7D1DAAFEECF951" bold="true" box="[199,332,1689,1714]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" reason="1">Discussion.</emphasis>
This species was described recently (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE44B2D5B77EC4CFD4B1DAAFC55F951" author="Dominguez, E. &amp; Molineri, C. &amp; Mariano, R." box="[753,1013,1689,1714]" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" pagination="29 - 44" refId="ref9820" refString="Dominguez, E., Molineri, C. &amp; Mariano, R. (2009) Revision of the South American species of Hagenulopsis Ulmer and Askola Peters (Ephemeroptera: Leptophlebiidae) with description of six new species. Zootaxa, 2142, 29 - 44." type="journal article" year="2009">
Domínguez 
<emphasis id="B901EACE5B77EC4CFCC61DA9FC14F951" box="[892,948,1689,1714]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) from the border of Colombia-Brazil, based only on male imagos. The female imago is described here for the first time, constituting the first record of the species for 
<collectingCountry id="F362764C5B77EC4CFEA51DD2FE36F919" box="[287,406,1761,1786]" name="Venezuela" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
. The female imagos were associated with the male imagos of this species because they present a very similar coloration (except that the blackish markings on the abdomen are somewhat wider). They can be separated from the female imagos of the other species of the genus mainly by the wing and abdominal coloration.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C36F65575B77EC4FFF7D1C42FC0BF968" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="303" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCA36DC5B77EC4FFF7D1C42FA88FE4E" blockId="1.[151,1437,1581,2038]" lastBlockId="2.[151,1436,151,429]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="303" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">
<emphasis id="B901EACE5B77EC4CFF7D1C42FEF9F869" bold="true" box="[199,345,1905,1930]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="302" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Female imago (in alcohol). Length: body, 6.3–6.5 mm; fore wing, 7.1–7.3 mm. General coloration (
<figureCitation id="134E2A595B77EC4CFEA31CA6FE24F84D" box="[281,388,1941,1966]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1552,1575]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetId="figure-312@2.[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Askola emmerichi, female imago. 1, dorsal view; 2, lateral view; 3, egg guide, ventral view, detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920668" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920668/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Figs. 1–2</figureCitation>
) thorax yellowish orange, abdomen yellowish with wide V-shaped black markings dorsally. Head (
<figureCitation id="134E2A595B77EC4CFF581C8AFE87F831" box="[226,295,1977,2002]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1552,1575]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetId="figure-312@2.[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Askola emmerichi, female imago. 1, dorsal view; 2, lateral view; 3, egg guide, ventral view, detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920668" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920668/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="302">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
) yellowish with black stripes around lateral and posterior margin of median ocellus and on posterior margin of head. Eyes black. Ocelli whitish, surrounded with black. Antennae yellowish. Thorax. Pronotum and metanotum yellowish white, heavily washed with black. Mesonotum yellowish orange with lateral margins of scutum and central area of scutellum, with the exception of its apex, blackish. Pleurae and sternae yellowish white, except sclerites close to base of legs darker. Legs I and III broken-off and missing. Leg II with segments yellowish white, tarsi and claws broken-off and missing. Wings (
<figureCitation id="134E2A595B74EC4FFCA61A37FCC5FEFE" box="[796,869,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1552,1575]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetId="figure-312@2.[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Askola emmerichi, female imago. 1, dorsal view; 2, lateral view; 3, egg guide, ventral view, detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920668" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920668/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
). Membrane hyaline, except base of Costal area yellowish and grayish spots around cross veins as in 
<figureCitation id="134E2A595B74EC4FFCBD1A14FCEFFEA3" box="[775,847,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1552,1575]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetId="figure-312@2.[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Askola emmerichi, female imago. 1, dorsal view; 2, lateral view; 3, egg guide, ventral view, detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920668" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920668/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
; longitudinal veins yellowish, cross veins blackish bordered with grayish; five costal cross veins from bulla to costal brace. Abdomen yellowish white. Terga with variable wide V shaped black markings as in 
<figureCitation id="134E2A595B74EC4FFD231A5CFD7CFE6B" box="[665,732,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1552,1575]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetId="figure-312@2.[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Askola emmerichi, female imago. 1, dorsal view; 2, lateral view; 3, egg guide, ventral view, detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920668" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920668/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
. Sterna without markings, except egg-guide yellowish orange, and its base grayish (
<figureCitation id="134E2A595B74EC4FFE381AA7FE66FE4E" box="[386,454,404,429]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–3" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1552,1575]" captionTargetBox="[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetId="figure-312@2.[166,1421,481,1531]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–3. Askola emmerichi, female imago. 1, dorsal view; 2, lateral view; 3, egg guide, ventral view, detail." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4920668" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4920668/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Caudal filaments yellowish white, with basal 1/6 of each segment blackish.
</paragraph>
