<subSubSection id="C36F65575B74EC4FFF7D1D89FB81F8FA" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8BCA36DC5B74EC4FFF7D1D89FB81F8FA" blockId="2.[151,1437,1614,1819]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">
<emphasis id="B901EACE5B74EC4FFF7D1D89FE8BF932" box="[199,299,1722,1747]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B901EACE5B74EC4FFF7D1D89FE84F930" bold="true" box="[199,292,1722,1747]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303">Ecology</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Imagos of this species were collected along the stream margins, at night, and during the rainy season (
<date id="FFCB101C5B74EC4FFF241DEDFEB7F914" box="[158,279,1758,1783]" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" value="2007-06">June 2007</date>
). The specific stream flows through the savanna area (
<quantity id="4C8D9B395B74EC4FFCCF1DEDFC6CF914" box="[885,972,1758,1783]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.308" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" unit="m" value="1308.0">1308 m</quantity>
) and it is a bed-rock, uncovered, medium size stream (
<quantity id="4C8D9B395B74EC4FFE991C31FEFDF8FA" box="[291,349,1794,1819]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" unit="m" value="30.0">30 m</quantity>
wide), with very shallow (~ 
<quantity id="4C8D9B395B74EC4FFD221C31FD41F8F8" box="[664,737,1794,1819]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="2" pageNumber="303" unit="cm" value="30.0">30 cm</quantity>
) and acidic (pH = 5) waters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
